title: Nasir beaten by unseeded England player in Surrey
text:
- Friday, October 23, 2015 - From Print Edition 
KARACHI: Pakistan’s top-ranked player Nasir Iqbal faced humiliation at the hands of an unseeded player in Men’s CLIC Sargent St George’s Hill Classic 2015 at St George’s Hill Lawn Tennis Club, Weybridge, Surrey, on Wednesday. 

Seventh seed Nasir was beaten by unseeded Charles Sharpes of England 5-11, 11-7, 11-8, 9-11, 14-16 in 80 minutes in the first round of this $25,000 event.
